ing conceived and perceived as inseparable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, Moderny19th century. 0aIllustrated periodicalszSpainzMadridxHistoryy19th century. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aMadrid.  aSpain.  acity life and urban culture.  aglobal modernities.  aillustrated press.  amodernity.  anineteenth century.  apopular and print culture.  asocial types and customs.  avisual culture and communication.1 aRodríguez-Galindo, Vanesa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614437940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526144379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526144379/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles